<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Opening (bars 1-7): Light 2-note RH, 3-note open LH. Joy motif keeps texture bright.
- Stanza 2 (bars 8-14): RH expands to 3 notes; LH adds doubled root for bars 8,11.
- Bridge (bars 15-23): Most varied: Fm(ii), Bb(V), alternating; G5 reached at bar 23 peak.
- Final section (bars 24-26): Return of Cm→Bb→Eb arc with full close.

NON-DIATONIC HANDLING:
- G major (bars 6,13,25) → Gm: harp plays G-Bb-D (iii in Eb), Bb4 explicit accid.ges.
- C major (bars 5,12,19) → Cm: harp plays C-Eb-G (vi in Eb).
- F major (bars 20,22) → Fm: harp plays F-Ab-C (ii in Eb), Ab explicit accid.ges.
- Bbm (bar 18) → Bb: harp plays Bb-D-F (V in Eb) — closer harmonic function.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bb4 sustains as common tone in RH from Eb(bar1) into Cm(bar2) beat 1
- Bridge descent in pedal (bars 15→16): Eb→Bb→C→F stepwise
- Bar 22→23: Fm→Bb→Eb, LH voice Ab3→A(nat)→Bb — minor inflection smoothly resolved
- Final: e5b melody note at peak (bar 26) mirrored by Eb1 in pedal — octave unison

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-7: Sparse (joyful waltz feel), 2-note RH, 3-note LH
- Bars 8-14: Fuller RH (3 notes), LH with doubled root
- Bars 15-23: Most active — 3 chord changes in some bars, bridge exploration
- Bars 24-26: Climactic: G5 reached, then full Eb root-pos close
-->
